uientry.unicode: You will find all the details you need to manage this province on this panel.
This shows what global factors are increasing, or hindering growth in this province.|| As a province grows, it will be able to support construction of larger castles.

Total growth this turn||This is the amount that your total region wealth will increase next turn.||This number is the result of the negative and positive factors to the left.||Move your cursor over the icons to the left for more information.
This is a prediction of next season's overall growth, calculated using the global factors above.

Global food surplus determines how much food is distributed amongst a clan's provinces, which in turn affects their growth.||A negative surplus can result in food shortages in provinces that have a negative food contribution.
This shows the amount of town growth caused by certain town buildings.

state.unicode: This shows how many ports a province has, which affects the amount of town growth.

uientry.unicode: Mastery of the arts also contributes to provincial growth.||You can see your clan's progress in this by viewing the Mastery of the Arts panel.
This is the effect of your global tax rate on this province.||You can change the tax rate on the Finances panel.

state.unicode: This factor includes your clan's diplomatic deals, trade and special bonuses.

uientry.unicode: You must keep an eye on public order to prevent riots and rebellions, particularly if it is a province you have recently captured.||The pips below show what is affecting public order, positively and negatively.||Order can be kept by keeping the population happy or by repressing them with authority!

state.unicode: Neutral||The population are neither unhappy nor completely under your control.||You may wish to take steps to improve your control over them, such as increasing repression.
Unhappy||The population is unhappy and could easily riot and rebel.||Increase repression in this area to keep things from getting worse.
Under control||The population is either happy, or too scared of you to do anything!||Although both will keep order in your province, a happy population will increase town growth.

uientry.unicode: Total public order||This is based on the positive and negative factors to the right.||The icon to the left shows the public order status for this province.
The positive effects on your population's public order.||Mouse over the pips to see more details.
The negative effects on your population's public order.||Mouse over the pips to see more details.
This section shows the factors contributing to this province's wealth.
The more wealth a province generates, the greater the tax income from it.
The more wealth a province generates, the greater your clan's tax income.
High tax rates will generate a greater income from this province, but also make the population less happy.||Tax rates are global, but you can change your tax rate in the Finance panel.

uientry.s:
local this = UIComponent(Address) local parent = UIComponent(this:Parent("region_info"))
function OnMouseOn() parent:LuaCall("OnMouseOnTaxIncome") end
function OnMouseOff() parent:LuaCall("OnMouseOffTaxIncome") end

uientry.unicode: This shows the income gained from this province, determined by the global tax rate.

Total treasury income||The amount that this region contributes to your funds every year.||It is calculated using your region wealth and your total tax rate.||Increase this number by raising taxes or increasing region wealth.
This is the accumulated wealth produced by the province's farming.

state.unicode: This is the accumulated wealth produced by the province's resources.
This is the accumulated wealth produced by the province's commerce.

uientry.unicode: This is the accumulated wealth of the province's towns. It will grow each turn by the combined town growth to the right.
This is the accumulated wealth of the province's towns. It will grow each turn by the combined town growth to the right.

This is the accumulated wealth produced by the province's commerce.

uientry.unicode: This shows the province's religious followings and any specialities it may have.
Province specialities provide bonuses when developed.

state.unicode: Province specialities provide bonuses when developed.

uientry.unicode: Population||This is the current total population of this region.||The section to the left shows the influences on population growth.
You will have more public order with populations that follow your national religion.||You can use your missionaries to start converting a region by moving them into that area.
Religion affects a province's public order.||A province that follows the official clan religion will be easier to control.
Food is an important factor in local and global growth.||See the factors below for more details.
Food is an important factor in local and global growth.||See the factors below for more details.

Local produce is used to feed a province's population.||Any remaining food is added toward the clan's global food surplus.||A negative number will mean the province will have to rely more heavily on the global food surplus.
The greater the size of the castle, the more food required to sustain its population.
This is added to the global food surplus, which helps increase global provincial growth.
Exempting a province from tax may boost your population's happiness.||This is an effective way of dealing with an unruly region, and could stop any riots that have started or may be brewing.
